body.description: Our Field Day Baby Wipes will soothe and moisturize your babys skin with natural Aloe Vera and Vitamin E. Theyre alcohol free to prevent dryness and hypoallergenic to protect even the most sensitive of skin. Its the high quality youve come to expect from Field Day for the most precious stage of life. Baby Wipes Will Soothe And Moisturize Your Babys Skin With Natural Aloe Vera And Vitamin E. Alcohol Free To Prevent Dryness And Hypoallergenic To Protect Even The Most Sensitive Of Skin. One wipe for everything - use Expressions Multi-Use Wipes on body, face, messes, surfaces, and more. Gentle enough for faces, yet durable enough for tough messes. Pop-top dispenses just one wipe at a time so you only get what you need.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 2, 2013
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great wipes, priced to high
reviews.reviewText: These are the best natural baby wipes I have used. No chemical odor smell. Great texture. Only complaint is these are priced very high. I can order the same 12 pack from my co-op for 34.00.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 28, 2020
reviews.reviewText: My mother in assisted living uses these. She gets a full shower/bath 2x a week, due to dry skin. These are quite large and she feels refreshed when using this brand between baths- she feels they get her quite clean using just one. Also, her skin doesn’t feel dry after using, and no heavy scent- just clean.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 14, 2016
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Wonderful, soft wipes.
reviews.reviewText: I discovered these baby wipes recently after my go-to, Earth's Best, changed their (previously) awesome wipes to a massively inferior product. Based on the recommendations of other customers, I ordered a box of these wipes, and am delighted. They are gentle, soft, have ample lotion, and do not irritate. I highly recommend them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 18, 2020
reviews.reviewText: Not my favorite wipes. Did not like the texture or ease of use. Also feel they are overpriced.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 22, 2019
reviews.reviewText: Great for my sensitive skin, no rash, burning or breakout !

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 15, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars I was stupid for buying this thinking it was a four-pack
reviews.reviewText: I was stupid for buying this thinking it was a four-pack. Ridiculously overpriced for mediocre product and just a "refill".
